Websockets actually work-

Step 1: How WebSocket actually starts

👉 It begins as an HTTP request
GET /chat HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade
Sec-WebSocket-Key: abc123
Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13

👉 Server responds:
HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade


Step 2: After connection (Real Magic 🔥)

👉 No more HTTP
👉 Just messages flowing both ways
🔹 Example Flow (Chat System)
🟢 Client connects
const socket = new WebSocket("wss://example.com/chat");
🟢 Send message
socket.send(JSON.stringify({
  type: "SEND_MESSAGE",
  conversationId: "123",
  message: "Hello"
}));
🟢 Receive message
socket.onmessage = (event) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
  console.log("Received:", data);
};



